Subject: Cal Low Cost Torque Wrench 

Hi All,

I use low cost torque wrenches (low , med and high). They are the click 
type. I developed crude calibration curves on the low and med wrenches to  
help off set rather large errors.

I really don't know how my cheap junk compares to the more costly tools. In 
either case they probably need to be calibrated.

This is the data from my first calibration. From time to time I check a 
point to be sure it has not shifted and they have held so far. I am not 
looking for perfection here, just to be close enough.

		Small Torque Wrench Chart
Dial In/Lb	Calc In/Lb	Calc Ft/Lb	Dial Ft/Lb	Meas End	Error %		Date: 2Sept98
35	19.50	1.63	2.92	2	-44.29
